	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001080_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'--> 
<!--Hand 01 71 top left--><!--hand 02 91798 top right-->
<lb/>My book is delayed till November
<lb/>on account of these said hideous affairs
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear Captain</p>
<lb/><p>Murray is 
<lb/>willing to print 
<lb/>250 copies but 
<lb/>thinks that as 
<lb/>the majority of 
<lb/>readers care 
<lb/>little for these 
<lb/>details, it had 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001080_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'--> 
<lb/>Will you ask the Admiral's opinion
<lb/>and tell me where they will be published
<lb/>if not in the way Murray proposes 
<lb/>
<lb/>better not be 
<lb/>put into the 
<lb/>book, but 
<lb/>given to whoever 
<lb/>may apply 
<lb/>for it. In 
<lb/>these circumstances 
<lb/>what is to be 
<lb/>done. Shall 
<lb/>we give them 
<lb/>over to the 
<lb/>Royal Geographical 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001080_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'--> 
<lb/>so that I may refer to them in
<lb/>my preface <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>I am &amp; David Livingstone
<lb/>
<lb/>or Astronomical 
<lb/>Society. I should  
<lb/>like the Admiral's 
<lb/>opinion: 12 000 
<lb/>is a serious 
<lb/>expense though 
<lb/>it would only 
<lb/>be two sheets 
<lb/>At any rate 
<lb/>you are in 
<lb/>for the Editorship 
<lb/>&amp; I am thankful 
<lb/>that you are</p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001080_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'--> 
<!--hand 02 91798 top right-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">When will you 
<lb/>be back? I 
<lb/>go to Dublin on 
<lb/>Thursday morning</p>
<lb/><p>I here leave 
<lb/>all I have of  
<lb/><unclear cert="medium">Maclear</unclear> in 
<lb/>a duplicate which 
<lb/>I intend to deposit 
<lb/>after you have 
<lb/>done with it where 
<lb/>I found it. I leave 
<lb/>also a <add place="above">rough</add> proof of 
<lb/>Arrowsmith.</p>
			
